'''Ezras Izrael Synagogue''' was a synagogue in [[Łódź]], [[Poland]]. It was built in [[1899]]-[[1904]], designed by [[Gustaw Landau-Gutenteger]]. The synagogue was burnt down by [[Nazis]] in November [[1939]].

